    "summary": "Maria Tomai is a Ph.D. Fellow at the United Nations University- Maastricht Economic and Social Research Institute on Innovation and Technology (UNU-MERIT). Her research is focused on sustainability transitions and circular economy in developing country cities. Maria is looking into transition pathways for cities to develop sustainable waste management systems. She follows a transdisciplinary research approach, employing participatory scenario planning and system dynamics modelling, along with systems thinking and socio-technical transitions theories.\nAdditionally, she is studying the role of environmental education and other nudge innovations, to drive behavioural change towards a circular economy. \n\nMaria is also a member of SITE4Society, co-organising local and international workshops on the SDGs, Circular Economy and other relevant topics. She is also engaged in voluntary activities, managing international WASH+ (Water, Sanitation, Hygiene, Waste Management) projects and supervising volunteers at Friend in Need (India).",
